# Arming the {DOMAIN}-janitor (pick one — enabling is one step)

The never-stale safety net is only real once the janitor runs on a schedule. If no scheduler exists at
build time, record the cadence in `operations/routines.md` AND drop one of the snippets below so the
user can enable it with a single copy. Default cadence: **weekly, Monday 09:00**. After enabling, note
it in `operations/routines.md` so the doctor's "schedule armed" check passes.

## Option A — GitHub Actions (if the workspace is a GitHub repo)
Save as `.github/workflows/{DOMAIN_SLUG}-janitor.yml`. Needs an agent CLI + API key available to CI.

```yaml
name: {DOMAIN_SLUG}-janitor
on:
  schedule:
    - cron: "0 9 * * 1"        # Mondays 09:00 UTC
  workflow_dispatch: {}
jobs:
  janitor:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    steps:
      - uses: actions/checkout@v4
      - name: Run the {DOMAIN}-janitor skill
        env:
          ANTHROPIC_API_KEY: ${{ secrets.ANTHROPIC_API_KEY }}
        run: |
          # wire your agent runner here, e.g.:
          # npx @anthropic-ai/claude-code -p "Run the {DOMAIN}-janitor skill" --permission-mode acceptEdits
          echo "invoke the {DOMAIN}-janitor via your agent runner"
      - name: Commit any reconciliation
        run: |
          git config user.name  "{DOMAIN}-janitor"
          git config user.email "janitor@users.noreply.github.com"
          git add -A && git commit -m "chore: scheduled {DOMAIN}-janitor reconcile" || echo "nothing to reconcile"
          git push || true
```

## Option B — cron (Linux / macOS)
`crontab -e`, then (adjust the path + your agent CLI):

```cron
0 9 * * 1 cd {workspace} && <agent-cli> -p "Run the {DOMAIN}-janitor skill" >> operations/janitor.log 2>&1
```

## Option C — launchd (macOS, survives reboots)
Save as `~/Library/LaunchAgents/local.{DOMAIN_SLUG}.janitor.plist`, then `launchctl load` it:

```xml
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<plist version="1.0"><dict>
  <key>Label</key><string>local.{DOMAIN_SLUG}.janitor</string>
  <key>ProgramArguments</key>
  <array><string>/bin/sh</string><string>-c</string>
    <string>cd {workspace} &amp;&amp; &lt;agent-cli&gt; -p "Run the {DOMAIN}-janitor skill"</string>
  </array>
  <key>StartCalendarInterval</key><dict>
    <key>Weekday</key><integer>1</integer><key>Hour</key><integer>9</integer><key>Minute</key><integer>0</integer>
  </dict>
</dict></plist>
```

## Option D — agent-runner scheduled task
If your agent runner has native scheduled tasks, create one that runs the `{DOMAIN}-janitor` weekly.
